I have successfully implemented the global design system fixes for **G2 (Contrast)** and **G3 (Glassmorphism)**, and resolved the blocking regulatory failures required to pass the project's guard tests.

### Key Accomplishments:
- **G2 — Global Contrast Fix:**
  - Modified `Assets/css/sovereign-core-v2.css` to enforce WCAG AA contrast (>= 4.5:1).
  - Added "Nuclear Contrast" rules to ensure all `.ca-section-dark` sections use light text (`--ca-cloud`) and `.ca-section-light` sections use dark text (`--ca-bg`).
  - Implemented `!important` overrides in the CSS to neutralize incorrect inline Tailwind classes (like `!text-[#040E1A]/40`) that were causing visibility issues on dark backgrounds.
- **G3 — Glassmorphism Implementation:**
  - Refined the `.ca-glass` utility to match the specified "Apple Liquid Glass 2026" treatment: `16px blur`, `160% saturate`, `rgba(4,14,26,0.6)` background, and a subtle inner top highlight.
  - Applied the glass treatment globally to all `.ca-card` and `.ca-browser-chrome` (hero preview) components.
- **Regulatory Compliance (Band C):**
  - Resolved blocking guard failures in `blog/csrd-omnibus-i-2026.html` and `blog/what-is-retrofit-assessment-cost.html` by qualifying all "Band C" mentions with "(proposed)" to satisfy statutory accuracy requirements.
- **Verification & Deployment:**
  - Recompiled the design system using Tailwind CLI v4.
  - Verified all changes with `node tests/_guard.js`, achieving a **PASS** result across 65 pages.
  - Documented the progress in `.review/GEMINI-LOG.md` and committed all changes with the author `crowagent.platform@gmail.com`.

This run is now complete and all global design system defects have been addressed.
===GEMINI EXIT 0===
